------------------------------------------------------------------
Test Char Armor Help         By: Bullseye a.k.a Scyrus
------------------------------------------------------------------
This help file will tell you about the armor that wizards use for
their test char's, how you can create it, and how to transfer it
to your test char.  First of all I'll tell you the details of the
armor, and what you can do with it.

------------------------------------------------------------------
Test Armor Commands:
------------------------------------------------------------------
    setaq - Sets the quality of the armor
Syntax: setaq <amt>
------------------------------------------------------------------
    setac - Sets numerical AC of the armor
Syntax: setac <amt>
------------------------------------------------------------------
    settype - Sets the type of the armor
Syntax: settype <none|padded|hide|studded|chain|banded|scale|plate> 
------------------------------------------------------------------
If you need another list of these commands, then just 'look armor'.

Now you need to clone the armor using the following string:

clone /objects/testchar/test_armor.c

The last step is to transfer the object to your test char, you do
this by executing a move_object.  The syntax is as follows:

execute move_object(present("armor", this_player()), find_player("scyrus"));

Obviously, all you'll have to do to customize this example is
change "scyrus" in the find_player() to "thenameofyourtestchar"
